[0.000, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;73r\u001b8\u001b[73d"]
[0.000, "o", "\n\u001b[1;75r\u001b[72;1H; Mapping base of shared memory segments (for Windows only). All the PHP\u001b[72;33H"]
[0.032, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;73r\u001b8\r\u001b[73d"]
[0.000, "o", "\n\u001b[1;75r\u001b[72;1H; processes have to map shared memory into the same address space. This\u001b[72;33H"]
[0.032, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;73r\u001b8\r\u001b[73d"]
[0.000, "o", "\n\u001b[1;75r\u001b[72;1H; directive allows to manually fix the \"Unable to reattach to base address\"\u001b[72;33H"]
[0.032, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
