[0.000, "o", "; your OS has problems with many files in one directory, and is\u001b[2;33H"]
[0.031, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;72r\u001b8\r\u001bM\u001b[1;75r\u001b[2;1H"]
[0.000, "o", "; store the session data in those directories.  This is useful if\u001b[2;33H"]
[0.031, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;72r\u001b8\r"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001bM\u001b[1;75r\u001b[2;1H"]
[0.000, "o", "; /path, what this will do is use subdirectories N-levels deep, and\u001b[2;33H"]
[0.032, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;73r\u001b8\r"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001bM\u001b[1;75r\u001b[2;1H"]
[0.000, "o", "; where N is an integer.  Instead of storing all the session files in\u001b[2;33H"]
[0.032, "o", "\u001b[?25l\u001b[?1c\u001b[?25h\u001b[?0c"]
[0.000, "o", "\u001b7\u001b[2;72r\u001b8\r"]
[0.001, "o", "\u001bM\u001b[1;75r\u001b[2;1H"]
[0.000, "o", ";"]
